com.da.antiphish.analyse

Class ScoreSafetyLimitSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.da.antiphish.analyse.ScoreSafetyLimitSelector

  • public class ScoreSafetyLimitSelector
extends Object
    ScoreSafetyLimitSelector is responsible for checking all single task scores against their safety limits according to values stored in configuration (config.json). If multiple safety limits are overrun, altogether three different methods are available for selecting overall result:
    • takeFirst(): takes the first exceedance of safety limit as result
    • takeHighestConfidence(): takes the exceedance of safety limit which's corresponding task has the highest confidence as result
    • takeMajority(): takes the majority of all exceedances of safety limits as result
    Author:
    Marco Madritsch

      • takeFirst

        public double takeFirst(List<TaskResult> taskResults)
        Checks for each task result if the score is above it's upper safety limit or under it's lower safety limit and selects the first found exceedance as result.
        Parameters:
        taskResults - list of all TaskResult objects
        Returns:
        the safety limit result, 0.0 if first found exceedance is an exceedance of lower limit, 1.0 if first found exceedance is an exceedance of upper limit, -1.0 if no exceedance was found or an error occurred

      • takeHighestConfidence

        public double takeHighestConfidence(List<TaskResult> taskResults)
        Checks for each task result if the score is above it's upper safety limit or under it's lower safety limit and selects the exceedance which's corresponding task has the highest confidence as result.
        Parameters:
        taskResults - list of all TaskResult objects
        Returns:
        the safety limit result, 0.0 if exceedance with highest task confidence is an exceedance of lower limit, 1.0 if exceedance with highest task confidence is an exceedance of upper limit, -1.0 if no exceedance was found or an error occurred

      • takeMajority

        public double takeMajority(List<TaskResult> taskResults)
        Checks for each task result if the score is above it's upper safety limit or under it's lower safety limit and selects the majority of all exceedance of safety limits as result.
        Parameters:
        taskResults - list of all TaskResult objects
        Returns:
        the safety limit result, 0.0 if there are more exceedances of lower limits than exceedances of upper limits, 1.0 if there are more exceedances of upper limits than exceedances of lower limits, -1.0 if no exceedance was found or an error occurred
